{"builder": {"source": "x", "name": "Andrej Karpathy", "handle": "karpathy", "bio": "I like training large deep neural nets.", "tweets": [{"id": "2069547676849557725", "text": "This is a new paradigm for interacting with Claude that is significantly more "inline" with all the other human activity org-wide. Once you do all of the under the hood engineering work to make this "just work" (e.g. across tools, integrations, compute environments, memory, security, etc.), Claude basically joins the team in a seamless way - you can talk to it as you would talk to a person and it can help with a very large variety of workloads.

Imo this is the 3rd major redesign of LLM UIUX. The first paradigm was that the LLM is a website you go to, the second was that it is an app you download to your computer. This third one is that it is a self-contained, persistent, asynchronous entity with org-wide tools and context, working alongside teams of humans. It really takes a while to wrap your head around it, but it works and it is awesome.", "createdAt": "2026-06-23T22:26:31.000Z", "url": "https://x.com/karpathy/status/2069547676849557725", "likes": 12492, "retweets": 974, "replies": 625, "isQuote": true, "quotedTweetId": "2069468693017268244"}]}, "tweets": [{"id": "2069547676849557725", "text": "This is a new paradigm for interacting with Claude that is significantly more "inline" with all the other human activity org-wide. Once you do all of the under the hood engineering work to make this "just work" (e.g. across tools, integrations, compute environments, memory, security, etc.), Claude basically joins the team in a seamless way - you can talk to it as you would talk to a person and it can help with a very large variety of workloads.

